-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Canyon Services Group, Emera, KP Tissue
-- 
-- Thu Mar 20, 2014 06:31AM EDT
-- None



March 20 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Canyon Services Group, Emera and KP Tissue, on Thursday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Canyon Services Grp <FRC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity ups to buy; Raymond James, CIBC up target * Emera Inc <EMA.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy * KP Tissue <KPT.TO>: RBC, CIBC lower target price on shares of the company  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Thursday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * Armtec Infrastructure <ARF.TO>: Raymond James cuts target price to C$2 from C$2.50 * Blackpearl Resources <PXX.TO>: Canaccord Genuity adds to its Canadian Focus List * Canyon Services Group <FRC.TO>: Raymond James raises target price to C$15.50 from C$15 * Canyon Services Group <FRC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises to buy from hold * Canyon Services Group <FRC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises price target to C$16 from C$14 * Canyon Services Group <FRC.TO>: CIBC raises target price to C$13.50 from C$12.50  * Emera Inc <EMA.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy * Finning International <FTT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to C$33.50 from C$31; buy  * Finning International <FTT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity removes from its Canadian Focus List * Intertain Group Ltd <IT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity starts with a speculative buy rating  * Intertain Group Ltd <IT.TO>: Canaccord Genuity starts coverage with target of C$5.75 * KP Tissue <KPT.TO>: CIBC cuts target price to C$20 from C$22 * KP Tissue <KPT.TO>: RBC cuts target price to C$19 from C$20; rating outperform * Lake Shore Gold <LSG.TO>: BMO raises price target to C$0.65 from C$0.50; underperform * RMP Energy <RMP.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$8.50; rating buy * Romarco Minerals <R.TO>: Paradigm raises target price to c$0.95 from c$0.75; spec buy * Westshore Terminals Investment <WTE.TO>: RBC cuts to sector perform from outperform